## 5. Temperature

**Two completely different pipelines:**

### Raw pipeline (Lightroom / Camera Raw / DNG — photographically correct)
```
Temp (Kelvin) + Tint  →  CIE xy chromaticity white point
                      →  interpolate ColorMatrix1/2 in inverse CCT (mired)
                      →  CameraNeutral vector
                      →  per-channel gains = 1 / CameraNeutral
                      →  apply as diagonal multiply in camera-native linear RGB
```
Defined in the **Adobe DNG Specification, Chapter 6**.  
⚠️ Kelvin values are NOT portable across raw converters.

### 8-bit sRGB / web shader (GPUImage / FrontShaders)
```glsl
const vec3 warmFilter = vec3(0.93, 0.54, 0.0);
// Step 1: YIQ tint shift (see §6)
vec3 yiq = RGBtoYIQ * source.rgb;
yiq.b = clamp(yiq.b + tint * 0.5226 * 0.1, -0.5226, 0.5226);
vec3 rgb = YIQtoRGB * yiq;
// Step 2: overlay-blend toward warm orange
vec3 processed = overlay(rgb, warmFilter);  // per-channel overlay formula
gl_FragColor = vec4(mix(rgb, processed, temperature), source.a);
```

