## 6. Tint

**Axis:** green ↔ magenta (perpendicular to temperature on the color wheel)

| Pipeline | Implementation |
|---|---|
| Raw (Lightroom) | Perpendicular offset off Planckian locus in CIE 1960 UCS |
| LAB intuition | Shifts the **a\*** axis (green−magenta) |
| Shader (GPUImage) | Shifts the **Q channel** in YIQ space |

```glsl
// YIQ tint shift
yiq.b = clamp(yiq.b + tint * 0.5226 * 0.1, -0.5226, 0.5226);
```

**Why two axes?** Temperature fixes blue↔red(yellow) casts (daylight vs. tungsten).  
Tint fixes green↔magenta casts (fluorescent lights, mixed sources).

