## 8. Divide-by-Zero Guards

The most common source of image-filter bugs.

### RGB → HSL / HSV

```
max  = max(R, G, B)
min  = min(R, G, B)
delta = max − min
```

| Division | When it's zero | Guard |
|---|---|---|
| Hue `÷ delta` | `delta=0` (gray pixels) | `if (max == min) { h = 0; s = 0; }` |
| HSL S `÷ (2 − max − min)` | L = 0 or 1 (black/white) | caught by the `max==min` branch |
| HSV S `÷ max` | `max=0` (pure black) | `if (max == 0) S = 0;` |
| Shadows/Highlights `÷ lum` | `lum=0` (pure black) | `if (lum < 1e-6) skip or return color` |

### Branchless GLSL (epsilon method — no `if` needed)
```glsl
vec3 rgb2hsv(vec3 c) {
    vec4 K = vec4(0.0, -1.0/3.0, 2.0/3.0, -1.0);
    vec4 p = mix(vec4(c.bg, K.wz), vec4(c.gb, K.xy), step(c.b, c.g));
    vec4 q = mix(vec4(p.xyw, c.r), vec4(c.r, p.yzx), step(p.x, c.r));
    float d = q.x - min(q.w, q.y);
    float e = 1.0e-10;            // ← epsilon prevents division by zero
    return vec3(abs(q.z + (q.w - q.y) / (6.0*d + e)), d / (q.x + e), q.x);
}

vec3 hsv2rgb(vec3 c) {
    // clamp(abs(mod(...)-3)-1) trick — zero division impossible
    vec3 rgb = clamp(abs(mod(c.x*6.0 + vec3(0,4,2), 6.0) - 3.0) - 1.0, 0.0, 1.0);
    return c.z * mix(vec3(1.0), rgb, c.y);  // no division at all
}
```

