## 9. Performance: LUTs & Approximations

| Technique | How it's used |
|---|---|
| **256-entry LUT** | Bake brightness/contrast/gamma curve into a lookup table; one array read per channel |
| **3D LUT texture** | Entire color grade (film emulation etc.) packed into a 3D RGB texture, sampled once per pixel |
| **Three box blurs** | W3C SVG spec mandates this as the `feGaussianBlur` approximation for large σ — within ~3% of true Gaussian |
| **Branchless step/mix** | Replace `if` with `step()` / `mix()` to avoid GPU warp divergence |
| **Smooth HSV** | `rgb = rgb*rgb*(3-2*rgb)` cubic smoothing inside hsv2rgb to hide banding |
| **Integer LUT for divide** | Embedded: precompute `round(255/170·I)` to avoid float divide in HSV |

